data.meta_description: Actor, Comedian. Born Jacob Rodney Cohen, a native of Long Island, New York, he was fortunate to have two starts in the show business industry. His first was in the 1940s appearing in the Borscht Belt resorts in the Catskill Mountains of New York state where he wrote jokes, was a singing waiter and did a stand up act...
